Update Your Information n                 Eyebrow menu Give Now UIC menu UIC edu Campus Map Isadore and Sadie Dorin Forum Ribbon Cutting Ceremony  n nShare this on Facebook n n n n n n Share this on Facebook  n nShare this on Twitter n n n n n n Share this on Twitter  n nShare this on Linked In n n n n n n Share this on Linked In Isadore and Sadie Dorin immigrated to the West side of Chicago from Russia as teenagers in the early      s  They met  married and built a successful business near what is now UIC  The Dorin Family Foundation  created by family members to honor their legacy  donated    million to UIC  The gift will establish a term naming of the UIC Isadore and Sadie Dorin Forum  which stands on a stretch of Roosevelt Road the young family often traveled  In addition  the gift will provide scholarships to undergraduate students with high academic achievement who graduated from a Cook County high school To honor this generous gift from the Dorin Family Foundation  we held a ribbon cutting ceremony to formally announce the term naming of the UIC Isadore and Sadie Dorin Forum and celebrate the legacy of the Dorin family Go to slide   Go to slide   Go to slide   Go to slide   Go to slide   Go to slide   Go to slide   Go to the next slide Go to the previous slide Go to the next slide Go to the previous slide Go to the next slide Go to the previous slide Go to the next slide Go to the previous slide Go to the next slide Go to the previous slide Go to the next slide Go to the previous slide Go to the next slide Go to the previous slide  n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n          Advancement n         Contact              advance uic edu Social Media Accounts  nFacebook n Facebook  nTwitter n Twitter  nInstagram n Instagram  nYouTube n YouTube UIC edu links UIC edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Event Calendar Job Openings Library Maps UIC Today UI Health Veterans Affairs Privacy Statement Campuses University o